WEBVTT

00:01.767 --> 00:03.033
I love the fall.

00:03.100 --> 00:05.633
Leaves turning colors,
ducks flying south.

00:05.700 --> 00:07.367
The return of corduroy.

00:07.433 --> 00:10.100
Life cycles reminding us
that everything must change.

00:10.967 --> 00:14.367
Here's Lizzie and her little friends,
"Whoever" and "Whatever."

00:14.600 --> 00:16.767
And that some things never will.

00:16.834 --> 00:19.266
My mom is making me invite
the whole class this year.

00:19.367 --> 00:21.266
Losers, too. Hit it.

00:21.633 --> 00:24.033
<i>Kate</i>

00:24.333 --> 00:25.900
<i>Kate will see you at the door</i>

00:25.967 --> 00:27.500
<i>Kate will free you, have some more</i>

00:27.567 --> 00:30.934
<i>Birthday cake and hit the dance floor</i>

00:31.000 --> 00:32.967
<i>It's going to be off the hizzie</i>

00:33.033 --> 00:34.600
<i>The Kate, the Kate, the Kate, the Kate</i>

00:34.667 --> 00:35.867
<i>-The, Kate, the Kate, the Kate</i>
<i>-The party, the party, the party</i>

00:35.934 --> 00:37.100
<i>-The, Kate, the Kate, the Kate</i>
<i>-The party, the party, the party</i>

00:37.166 --> 00:38.200
<i>-The, Kate, the...</i>
<i>-The party...</i>

00:38.266 --> 00:39.266
Huh!

00:39.900 --> 00:43.133
If they keep this up,
they're going to see my breakfast now.

00:49.300 --> 00:51.066
She's turning 14?

00:51.133 --> 00:52.633
-ALL: [CHANTING] Kate! Kate! Kate!
-GORDO: Man, impressive.

00:52.700 --> 00:54.867
Kate's got the whole school
chanting her name.

00:54.934 --> 00:56.633
[SCOFFS] Okay, I would not
go to this party

00:56.700 --> 00:57.834
if it were the last party on earth.

00:57.900 --> 01:00.133
Last year she gave us cell phones
in the goodie bags.

01:01.033 --> 01:03.266
-I am so there!
-Uh, me, too.

01:03.333 --> 01:06.367
-Wait, did that include long distance?
-Duh.

01:06.433 --> 01:07.834
Cell phone!

01:07.900 --> 01:09.900
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

01:12.367 --> 01:14.467
<i>If you believe</i>

01:15.867 --> 01:18.967
<i>We've got a picture-perfect plan</i>

01:19.400 --> 01:21.233
<i>We've got you fooled</i>

01:22.700 --> 01:26.600
<i>'Cause we only do the best we can</i>

01:28.100 --> 01:30.533
<i>And sometimes we make it</i>

01:31.734 --> 01:33.867
<i>And sometimes we fake it</i>

01:35.066 --> 01:40.600
<i>But we get one step closer</i>
<i>each and every day</i>

01:41.033 --> 01:44.066
<i>You will figure it out on the way</i>

01:51.600 --> 01:53.767
Mom, why can't you just be reasonable?

01:53.834 --> 01:55.900
I mean, why can't we
just talk about it?

01:55.967 --> 01:56.967
Talk away, honey,

01:57.066 --> 01:59.633
but you're not going to a party
where there's no chaperone.

01:59.700 --> 02:03.633
For the 900th time,
there will be a chaperone there.

02:03.700 --> 02:05.667
And for the 900th and first time,

02:05.734 --> 02:09.400
Kate's 18-year-old cousin Amy,
who plays in a band, doesn't count.

02:11.967 --> 02:14.100
Well, Kate's mom thinks it counts.

02:14.400 --> 02:17.533
Well, Kate's mom and your mom
have very different ideas

02:17.600 --> 02:18.867
about what is appropriate.

02:18.934 --> 02:21.700
That's because Kate's mom trusts her.
Ugh!

02:21.767 --> 02:24.333
Elizabeth Brooke McGuire!

02:24.400 --> 02:27.633
That tone has
"grounded" written all over it.

02:29.000 --> 02:30.300
Maintain, McGuire.

02:30.333 --> 02:32.800
Calmly explain to her
how important this is to you.

02:33.367 --> 02:35.233
Mom, everybody is going to be there.

02:35.300 --> 02:38.200
Everyone except
an appropriate chaperone,

02:38.266 --> 02:39.266
and you.

02:41.367 --> 02:43.266
Honey, why are you
in such a hurry to grow up?

02:43.333 --> 02:45.533
Can't you just be happy being a kid?

02:46.233 --> 02:49.033
How can I enjoy being a kid
when I can't go to any cool parties?

02:49.934 --> 02:52.033
Mom! Mom! We're going to be on TV!

02:52.100 --> 02:53.800
Really? Is there a new reality show?

02:53.867 --> 02:56.633
You know, The Real Stories
of the Really Clueless?

02:56.700 --> 02:59.734
You know, that was
actually very, very clever.

03:00.066 --> 03:02.734
Maybe when I'm a big star,
you can write for me.

03:02.800 --> 03:05.533
Oh, that'd be really cool
except for I wouldn't be able

03:05.600 --> 03:07.367
to go to any of those
cool premiere parties.

03:07.433 --> 03:10.333
You know why? Because there won't be
a chaperone there.

03:11.100 --> 03:14.400
Once again, I'm the worst mother
in the world.

03:14.467 --> 03:16.667
Cool, because I've been out
being fun dad.

03:16.734 --> 03:18.333
Only, the funniest.

03:18.734 --> 03:23.433
You're looking at the new spokesfamily
for Cardio Punch Sports Drink.

03:24.066 --> 03:26.967
This casting lady in the mall
picked us to be in a commercial.

03:27.266 --> 03:30.033
Spokesfamily? Where do we go?

03:30.500 --> 03:34.066
Um, actually, Mom,
when they said "spokesfamily,"

03:34.133 --> 03:38.667
what they really meant
was "spokesdad" and "spokesMatt."

03:39.000 --> 03:40.867
Oh, they don't need a mom?

03:41.133 --> 03:42.734
Sorry, it's a guy thing.

03:42.800 --> 03:44.133
-Yo!
-Yeah! Ha ha!

03:45.266 --> 03:46.700
No, really what should I wear?

03:46.767 --> 03:48.800
Honey, look on the bright side.
I get to do it.

03:48.867 --> 03:51.500
No, not you on-camera.

03:51.567 --> 03:53.767
You-you forgot to say "I do"

03:53.834 --> 03:56.767
when you saw Cousin Ree-Ree
with the video camera.

03:57.233 --> 03:58.266
Did not.

03:58.934 --> 04:01.967
I was blinded by your beauty.

04:02.033 --> 04:05.066
Sam, you flinched
for your driver's license picture.

04:05.133 --> 04:07.500
Look, honey, this is something
Matt really wants to do.

04:07.567 --> 04:10.033
I can get over being
a little camera shy for one day.

04:10.066 --> 04:12.834
That's why I am the "fun dad."

04:12.900 --> 04:15.033
[WHOOPING TRIUMPHANTLY]

04:17.300 --> 04:19.266
She started with my full name
and ended with,

04:19.333 --> 04:21.266
"Why can't you
just enjoy your childhood?"

04:21.433 --> 04:22.433
Fill in the blanks.

04:22.500 --> 04:26.100
Ugh. My mom gave me,
"I don't agree with Kate's mom

04:26.166 --> 04:27.700
"on how to raise children."

04:27.767 --> 04:30.633
"Raise!" Like we're chickens
or something!

04:31.200 --> 04:32.700
My mom said it was okay.

04:32.834 --> 04:33.834
BOTH: What?

04:33.900 --> 04:35.767
It's depressing, really.

04:35.834 --> 04:39.166
Do my parents think I'm so good
that I can never get into trouble?

04:39.734 --> 04:40.734
Yes.

04:40.967 --> 04:43.867
I can make trouble.
I have a dark side.

04:44.233 --> 04:46.467
I can disrespect the common areas.

04:46.533 --> 04:50.000
I can act without regard
for the safety of others. Hmm?

04:52.066 --> 04:53.066
Ow.

04:53.667 --> 04:55.567
Oh! Oh! I'm... I'm so sorry!

04:55.633 --> 04:56.967
Sorry, yet bad.

04:57.033 --> 04:58.467
L-let me get you a towel.

05:01.467 --> 05:04.233
Miranda, we cannot give up on this.
We have to go to this party.

05:04.300 --> 05:06.066
I mean, everyone is going to be there.

05:06.533 --> 05:09.000
Well, we could go back to them
and renegotiate.

05:09.066 --> 05:12.367
Like, minutes at the party,
for minutes of extra chores.

05:12.433 --> 05:13.967
Or minutes off the phone.

05:14.033 --> 05:16.233
Or minutes off the computer.

05:17.600 --> 05:18.867
Or minutes in jail!

05:19.967 --> 05:23.066
Why should we have to suffer to
exercise our constitutional right to

05:23.133 --> 05:24.333
the pursuit of happiness?

05:24.400 --> 05:25.834
It's simply un-American.

05:27.033 --> 05:28.033
Well, how 'bout this?

05:28.100 --> 05:30.633
Instead of not going to the party,
we just go.

05:31.333 --> 05:32.900
Our parents already said
that we couldn't.

05:33.767 --> 05:36.300
We do it anyway.
We just don't tell them.

05:36.967 --> 05:40.166
This sounds like it involves
a little bit of lying and deception.

05:40.500 --> 05:41.967
But a whole lot of going to the party.

05:42.867 --> 05:44.033
-I'm listening.
-[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

05:44.100 --> 05:45.133
Okay, well...

05:47.200 --> 05:51.367
Here we are, Dad,
the doorway to stardom!

05:51.433 --> 05:53.266
Okay, this is not
going to be that big a deal.

05:53.333 --> 05:54.633
I'm not going to
be on-camera that long.

05:54.700 --> 05:57.200
This is just going to be a fun day
together trying something new.

05:57.667 --> 06:00.300
Something new, like stardom!

06:00.367 --> 06:01.567
Here, let's just sign in.

06:02.033 --> 06:05.033
On the sign-in sheet to stardom!

06:05.100 --> 06:06.266
Will you stop doing that?

06:06.333 --> 06:09.900
There they are, the real father
and the real little boy

06:09.967 --> 06:11.266
I found in the shoe store.

06:11.333 --> 06:13.066
This is Steve, our director.

06:13.133 --> 06:16.000
-The man who'll direct us to star...
-Shh!

06:16.500 --> 06:19.333
Hi. Sam McGuire. This is my son, Matt.

06:19.400 --> 06:21.567
-Yo.
-Love them.

06:22.266 --> 06:24.100
Have the stunt guy
fit them with a harness.

06:24.166 --> 06:26.266
Robyn! Where's my blended?

06:26.900 --> 06:28.033
Did he say "harness"?

06:28.100 --> 06:30.633
The harness to stardom!

06:30.700 --> 06:32.967
-Stop doing that.
-MATT: Sorry.

06:37.200 --> 06:39.400
I'm really having second,
third, and fourth thoughts

06:39.467 --> 06:40.467
about this whole thing.

06:40.533 --> 06:43.433
Lizzie, you can't fall apart
at a time like this.

06:43.500 --> 06:44.600
At a time like what?

06:44.667 --> 06:46.667
At a time like the first time
that we tell our mothers

06:46.734 --> 06:49.333
that we're going to the mall
and we sneak to a party instead?

06:49.400 --> 06:51.600
This seems like a pretty good time
to fall apart to me.

06:51.667 --> 06:52.967
They'll never know.

06:53.033 --> 06:55.400
Mall, bus, party, bus mall.

06:55.467 --> 06:57.233
The plan is flawless.

06:58.200 --> 07:01.166
This plan is genius.
Sheer genius, I tell you.

07:01.233 --> 07:02.233
[LAUGHS]

07:02.300 --> 07:03.300
[COUGHING]

07:04.600 --> 07:05.600
What's the plan?

07:05.667 --> 07:07.800
Your plan is
your parents take you to the party

07:07.867 --> 07:09.533
that you're allowed to go to.

07:09.834 --> 07:11.100
Oh, but that's where you're wrong.

07:11.166 --> 07:13.767
See, I told my parents that
I wasn't going to the party tonight.

07:13.834 --> 07:16.100
In fact, they think
I'm at Miranda's house.

07:16.166 --> 07:18.633
But I'm not. I'm here.
Want to know why?

07:19.166 --> 07:20.400
'Cause I'm bad.

07:21.734 --> 07:22.967
We'll see you at the party, Gordo.

07:23.033 --> 07:25.467
No! You're not
getting rid of me that easily.

07:25.533 --> 07:27.500
'Cause I'm all about the plan tonight.

07:27.700 --> 07:28.700
Want to know why?

07:28.867 --> 07:30.867
Yeah, Gordo, you're bad.

07:31.767 --> 07:33.934
Ready, girls?
Gordo, you're coming, too?

07:34.000 --> 07:35.333
Oh, well, that's the plan.

07:38.867 --> 07:41.033
Lizzie, can I
talk to you for a minute?

07:41.900 --> 07:44.133
She knows. How does she always know?

07:44.600 --> 07:46.667
Um... s-sure, Mom.

07:47.033 --> 07:49.633
Um, I know you really wanted
to go to that party,

07:49.700 --> 07:52.300
and I'm sorry I had to say no,

07:52.600 --> 07:54.300
but I know you're going to
have a good time tonight

07:54.367 --> 07:55.667
at the mall with your friends.

07:56.767 --> 07:59.200
Please buy everybody
a big cookie on me.

08:01.467 --> 08:02.633
Thanks, Mom.

08:03.867 --> 08:05.900
[ROCK 'N' ROLL MUSIC PLAYING]

08:07.967 --> 08:08.967
Okay, it's official.

08:09.433 --> 08:11.266
I am the worst daughter
who ever lived.

08:11.800 --> 08:13.133
[SIGHS]

08:39.233 --> 08:40.867
-But she gives me $10.
-[LAUGHTER AND INDISTINCT CHATTER]

08:40.934 --> 08:42.500
I lie to her, and what does she do?

08:42.567 --> 08:44.300
She gives me $10!

08:44.367 --> 08:46.233
Lizzie, can you please
save the guilt thing

08:46.300 --> 08:47.467
until after the party?

08:47.867 --> 08:50.100
Trust me, knowing you,
it will still be there.

08:50.166 --> 08:52.033
Not for me. Guilt-free Gordo.

08:52.100 --> 08:54.367
You know why? 'Cause I'm bad.

08:54.600 --> 08:55.767
No, Gordo, because...

08:57.000 --> 08:58.400
'Cause you're allowed to be here.

09:03.467 --> 09:05.467
[UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING]

09:19.767 --> 09:21.133
-Football!
-[BOTH SHRIEK]

09:23.567 --> 09:25.834
Who are all of these people?

09:25.900 --> 09:26.900
Aah!

09:28.200 --> 09:29.734
-Whoo!
-[LIZZIE SCREAMS]

09:33.066 --> 09:35.300
-Miranda!
-Lizzie, hang on!

09:35.367 --> 09:38.367
Help! Gordo!

09:38.433 --> 09:39.767
Ooh, that looks bad.

09:40.967 --> 09:45.066
Help!

09:46.166 --> 09:48.133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

09:49.066 --> 09:51.333
Lizzie, hang on. Just go with it.

09:51.533 --> 09:52.533
Give me your hand.

09:57.200 --> 09:58.200
[PANTING]

09:58.266 --> 10:00.066
Wait, what is going on here?

10:00.133 --> 10:01.433
Total chaos.

10:01.500 --> 10:04.834
Let's ditch our coats
and see if we can find anyone we know.

10:05.333 --> 10:06.333
Over there.

10:11.400 --> 10:12.400
[BOTH GASP]

10:12.467 --> 10:13.467
Wait your turn.

10:13.533 --> 10:14.533
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

10:15.400 --> 10:17.066
I think that that was our chaperone.

10:21.200 --> 10:24.300
Son, I think I know
what the harness is for.

10:24.367 --> 10:26.834
This is the best day of my life.

10:27.033 --> 10:29.767
Listen, Matt, if the wall's
too high for you,

10:29.834 --> 10:31.233
we don't have to do this.

10:31.367 --> 10:34.033
Too high? It's not high enough!

10:34.100 --> 10:37.100
Oh, yeah, who's your rock climber?
Oh, yeah.

10:37.166 --> 10:38.166
Let's run over this.

10:38.233 --> 10:41.166
You scale the wall,
grab the Cardio Punch chug and smile.

10:41.233 --> 10:43.033
Repel back down the wall one-handed,

10:43.100 --> 10:45.433
with the bottle label out,
give me a flip at the end,

10:45.500 --> 10:48.500
touchdown and smile. Yes?

10:48.767 --> 10:51.467
This can't be safe.

10:51.867 --> 10:54.000
If it isn't, we'll fix it in editing.

10:54.066 --> 10:55.033
Robyn!

10:55.967 --> 10:58.200
I thought the whole school was coming.

10:58.266 --> 11:00.133
Did you guys see anyone you knew?

11:00.867 --> 11:03.867
I don't think so.
No one in our homeroom has beards.

11:04.133 --> 11:05.800
Maybe their parents
wouldn't let them come either.

11:05.934 --> 11:07.900
Oh, this is bad. All right, new plan.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.834
I say we go back to the mall,
split a giant cookie,

11:10.900 --> 11:11.900
and call it a night.

11:11.967 --> 11:13.633
-I'm there.
-[SPEAKING SPANISH]

11:13.700 --> 11:16.500
All right, on my count. One, two...

11:17.400 --> 11:18.400
[MIRANDA SCREAMS]

11:19.100 --> 11:21.200
Your seven minutes
was up ten minutes ago.

11:21.266 --> 11:23.633
Uh, don't worry, Kate,
we were just leaving.

11:23.700 --> 11:25.800
Yeah, h-happy birthday.
Thanks for inviting us.

11:25.867 --> 11:26.867
We had a great time.

11:29.166 --> 11:30.467
I can't believe
you guys are about to leave

11:30.533 --> 11:31.900
before all the cool people get here.

11:31.967 --> 11:34.500
Ah, well, that's us, big fat losers.

11:34.567 --> 11:35.567
-Yeah.
-Bye.

11:35.633 --> 11:36.633
Wait!

11:36.934 --> 11:38.900
Uh... We-we're just about
to cut the cake.

11:39.266 --> 11:40.934
Cake? T-there's cake!

11:41.033 --> 11:43.800
You-you guys there's cake. Cake, cake.

11:46.500 --> 11:48.867
-You said you wanted chocolate, right?
-Right.

11:49.333 --> 11:52.000
Phew. I got strawberry
'cause I like that better.

11:52.066 --> 11:53.667
I'm just glad
I remembered what you wanted.

11:54.400 --> 11:56.133
And where are the birthday candles?

11:56.200 --> 11:57.667
I was just told cake.

11:57.734 --> 11:59.700
Nobody said anything about candles.

11:59.767 --> 12:01.033
But it's my birthday.

12:01.100 --> 12:04.600
Oh, it is? Happy birthday.

12:05.834 --> 12:06.834
LIZZIE: Uh...

12:07.400 --> 12:10.333
I'm not going to lose my cool
over some little mistake, am I?

12:11.767 --> 12:13.900
No! Don't eat my cake!

12:13.967 --> 12:16.367
You guys haven't even
sung me <i>Happy Birthday</i> yet.

12:16.433 --> 12:17.900
BOY: Cake, cake, cake!

12:18.734 --> 12:19.867
[ALL GASP]

12:21.934 --> 12:24.233
Oh! This isn't happening!

12:24.700 --> 12:28.066
You know what? She-she's right.
I'm glad we didn't leave.

12:28.133 --> 12:30.233
-Oh, don't! Don't!
-Harsh.

12:31.333 --> 12:32.800
It's hard to tell
through the frosting,

12:32.867 --> 12:34.667
but Kate does look upset.

12:36.233 --> 12:38.166
Get away from me, you snakes!

12:39.266 --> 12:41.200
[ALL CHATTERING]

12:41.266 --> 12:42.967
Nobody deserves that
on their birthday.

12:43.533 --> 12:45.000
I'm going to go see if she's okay.

12:46.000 --> 12:48.934
And action! I said, action.

12:49.000 --> 12:51.033
Action. That means move.

12:51.100 --> 12:52.200
I can't move.

12:52.266 --> 12:54.633
Sure you can. Look. I'm in.

12:55.033 --> 12:56.033
I'm out.

12:56.700 --> 12:57.700
I'm in.

12:58.133 --> 12:59.133
I'm out.

12:59.200 --> 13:00.200
I'm in.

13:00.667 --> 13:01.734
Not helping.

13:02.066 --> 13:03.367
Dad, what's wrong?

13:03.700 --> 13:05.400
Bad rope-climbing incident.

13:06.800 --> 13:07.800
What do you mean?

13:07.867 --> 13:08.834
Too high.

13:10.734 --> 13:12.000
Action!

13:12.800 --> 13:15.200
-Dad are you afraid of heights?
-Uh-huh.

13:15.667 --> 13:17.133
Then why didn't you say so?

13:17.333 --> 13:18.667
I didn't want to let you down.

13:18.734 --> 13:20.867
People, you're not making me happy.

13:21.200 --> 13:23.633
One more time. Chug and smile.

13:23.834 --> 13:26.100
Dad you didn't have to do this for me.

13:26.166 --> 13:27.400
I know, but I wanted to.

13:27.467 --> 13:30.100
Hey, you, up there,
are you scared or just stupid?

13:30.166 --> 13:31.900
What did you just say?

13:32.266 --> 13:35.633
I wasn't talking to you, kid.
I was talking to the 180 pounds

13:35.700 --> 13:38.000
of useless fat hanging next to you.

13:38.066 --> 13:40.767
That's it. Dad...

13:40.834 --> 13:42.033
[MIMICKING TERMINATOR]
I'll be back.

13:50.266 --> 13:53.000
[IN NORMAL VOICE] Hey, buddy.
That's the best dad in the world

13:53.066 --> 13:55.467
hanging up there,
and you aren't even good enough

13:55.533 --> 13:57.800
to point your little cameras at him.

13:58.066 --> 14:00.233
So, listen up.
This is how it's going to work.

14:00.600 --> 14:02.633
You're going to stop yelling at my dad

14:02.700 --> 14:04.900
and I'll let you keep your kneecaps!

14:05.400 --> 14:07.567
-Yes?
-Yes.

14:07.633 --> 14:12.900
Now, cut him loose, get me a blended,
and that's a wrap.

14:14.667 --> 14:15.633
[SNIFFLES]

14:18.400 --> 14:19.400
[CHEERING]

14:19.467 --> 14:21.400
Let's hear it for my dad!

14:23.934 --> 14:25.033
Did you get that?

14:27.567 --> 14:30.867
I know what time it is,
but this is a big thing, Mom.

14:31.033 --> 14:33.033
Mom, they pushed me into my own cake.

14:33.867 --> 14:35.667
They didn't even sing <i>Happy Birthday.</i>

14:36.000 --> 14:39.300
No, she used my birthday party
to invite all of her friends.

14:40.200 --> 14:41.367
Maybe if you were here

14:41.433 --> 14:43.433
some of my friends
would have been allowed to come.

14:44.867 --> 14:49.033
Mom, can't you just
please come home? Hello?

14:49.600 --> 14:51.767
Mom, you're breaking up.
Can you hear me?

14:58.467 --> 14:59.734
Go away!

15:05.066 --> 15:07.500
-Are you okay?
-Do I look okay?

15:07.567 --> 15:09.467
You look like you could use some help.

15:09.533 --> 15:11.900
Wrong again, McGuire.
I don't need your help.

15:12.533 --> 15:13.734
This is going nowhere.

15:13.800 --> 15:16.133
And there's a big cookie at the mall
with my name on it.

15:16.800 --> 15:19.734
Okay, whatever.
Happy birthday. I'm out.

15:20.300 --> 15:21.400
[GLASS SHATTERING]

15:22.200 --> 15:23.200
[SIGHS]

15:25.367 --> 15:26.367
Uh...

15:29.300 --> 15:32.934
Kate, is this the party
that you wanted?

15:34.100 --> 15:35.867
I wanted a few friends for movies

15:35.934 --> 15:38.066
but then my mom said
I should have a grown-up party

15:38.133 --> 15:39.567
and then she left town.

15:39.633 --> 15:42.166
So now I'm stuck with
100 of my cousin's closest friends.

15:43.467 --> 15:45.734
Kate, we came to see you.

15:45.800 --> 15:47.367
Not entirely true, but...

15:48.767 --> 15:51.867
Here I am.
You must love seeing me like this.

15:51.934 --> 15:55.200
Actually, I do.
I like seeing you as a normal person.

15:57.800 --> 16:00.233
You know what? My mom's picking us up
at the mall at 10:00.

16:00.600 --> 16:01.900
Why don't you ditch all of this

16:01.967 --> 16:04.133
and come see a movie
with a few friends?

16:04.734 --> 16:06.400
-Really?
-Sure.

16:10.433 --> 16:11.667
Oh, hey, you guys.

16:11.734 --> 16:13.734
Kate's going to come
see a movie with us, okay?

16:13.800 --> 16:14.934
What are we going to see?

16:17.066 --> 16:20.033
Oh, man. Kate Sanders
is coming with us to the mall

16:20.100 --> 16:21.367
was not part of the plan.

16:27.333 --> 16:30.266
Lizzie, you guys go ahead.
I can't leave my house this way.

16:37.633 --> 16:39.266
Don't do that! Give me that!

16:39.900 --> 16:43.567
I'm positive that helping Kate play
keep-away with the statues

16:43.633 --> 16:44.934
wasn't part of the plan.

16:45.000 --> 16:46.633
We cannot leave her like this, guys.

16:46.700 --> 16:48.633
Uh, she hates us. We can leave her.

16:48.700 --> 16:51.133
I totally agree. Want to know why?

16:51.800 --> 16:53.367
-'Cause I'm bad.
-[SCOFFS]

16:53.433 --> 16:54.734
And this party's worse.

16:54.800 --> 16:56.834
You're right. You know what,
this party needs a mom.

16:56.900 --> 16:58.266
So, I'm going to go call mine.

16:58.333 --> 17:01.734
Uh, what? Uh, Lizzie,
let's get that big cookie in you quick

17:01.800 --> 17:02.934
'cause you're talking crazy!

17:03.000 --> 17:05.133
No, it's the right thing
to do, Miranda.

17:05.200 --> 17:06.533
But we'll be so grounded.

17:06.600 --> 17:08.567
No, after our parents
see how mature we've been

17:08.633 --> 17:10.166
through this whole thing,
they'll be so proud,

17:10.233 --> 17:11.667
we'll be completely off the hook.

17:11.734 --> 17:13.767
That never works. Never.

17:13.834 --> 17:16.333
You always think it's gonna,
but then it doesn't.

17:17.333 --> 17:19.333
-[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]
-[PHONE RINGING]

17:21.467 --> 17:22.467
Hello?

17:24.333 --> 17:28.000
Yeah? Okay, you need me?

17:28.834 --> 17:30.233
Okay, I'll be right there.

17:30.433 --> 17:31.767
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

17:34.033 --> 17:35.000
Kids.

17:36.133 --> 17:38.066
-Are you okay?
-We're fine, Mom.

17:38.400 --> 17:40.033
I'm glad you called me.

17:40.800 --> 17:42.967
These are the times
when I love her so much.

17:43.500 --> 17:45.567
Mom, I know that you said
we shouldn't be here.

17:45.633 --> 17:46.633
You were right.

17:46.700 --> 17:49.700
And you were right about the chaperone
not being a chaperone.

17:50.200 --> 17:52.667
But I've learned my lesson,
so there's no need to punish me.

17:52.734 --> 17:54.800
Oh, okay, I'm glad
you've still got your sense of humor

17:54.867 --> 17:55.934
'cause you're going to need it

17:56.000 --> 17:58.233
during your long,
lonely days of being grounded.

17:58.300 --> 18:01.033
Miranda, Gordo, I'm going to
miss seeing you at the house.

18:01.200 --> 18:03.967
Um, actually, Mrs. McGuire,
I'm allowed to be here.

18:04.066 --> 18:06.200
Oh really? Not after I finish
talking to your parents.

18:07.367 --> 18:09.233
That never works either.

18:09.300 --> 18:12.200
Mom, can you take all of this
and send it that way?

18:12.266 --> 18:14.367
Oh, I'm just warming up.
This is going to be fun.

18:15.600 --> 18:18.533
And then there are times
when she really, really scares me.

18:19.400 --> 18:20.400
[LION ROARS]

18:20.467 --> 18:22.500
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

18:43.300 --> 18:44.700
[MUSIC STOPS]

18:45.600 --> 18:47.000
[ALL EXCLAIMING]

18:47.667 --> 18:49.100
Now, hear this, people.

18:49.467 --> 18:51.100
You don't have to go home,

18:51.166 --> 18:53.400
but you have to
get the heck out of here!

18:53.467 --> 18:54.767
Excuse me, uh, ma'am.

18:54.834 --> 18:56.500
You're kind of, like,
stopping the party.

18:56.567 --> 18:57.567
Exactly.

18:58.033 --> 19:01.367
-But that would, like, stop the party.
-Right.

19:01.433 --> 19:03.367
Hmm, so the party's
going to be over now?

19:03.433 --> 19:06.633
-Right now!
-Oh, and you are?

19:06.700 --> 19:11.033
Me? I am your worst nightmare.

19:11.300 --> 19:15.667
I am a mother on a mission
and I hope you think I'm kidding.

19:16.367 --> 19:18.834
Now, move, people!

19:22.133 --> 19:23.133
[EXHALES]

19:24.633 --> 19:26.867
Bye-bye. Bye-bye.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.200
Oh, I'll take that. Yeah, thanks.

19:29.266 --> 19:30.600
Buckle up for safety.

19:31.333 --> 19:32.333
Here.

19:33.500 --> 19:35.033
So you want to
come home with us, sweetie?

19:35.100 --> 19:37.166
I think I'm okay, now.

19:37.433 --> 19:38.700
Thanks, Mrs. McGuire.

19:38.867 --> 19:41.734
What a way to celebrate
your 15th birthday, huh?

19:41.800 --> 19:45.533
-Um, actually, it's my 14th.
-Right.

19:51.266 --> 19:52.667
Uh, "Thanks, Lizzie."

19:53.834 --> 19:56.967
I know that you'll deny it
even under alien water torture.

19:57.800 --> 20:00.266
Just so we're clear, thanks, Lizzie.

20:01.133 --> 20:02.300
Don't mention it.

20:03.100 --> 20:04.667
Glad that's behind us.

20:12.300 --> 20:13.367
Cake.

20:14.834 --> 20:16.667
GORDON: So, this is
being grounded, huh?

20:16.900 --> 20:18.533
MIRANDA: Yeah. It reeks.

20:18.600 --> 20:20.633
I know, I am so bored.

20:20.700 --> 20:22.800
Yeah, well, I have gotten
a lot of work done.

20:22.867 --> 20:26.066
Well, it's official.
You're no longer bad, Gordo.

20:26.133 --> 20:28.734
Lizzie, come downstairs.
Matt and Dad's commercial's on.

20:29.300 --> 20:31.734
[SIGHS]
I got to go. More joy.

20:31.800 --> 20:33.033
-[LINE DISCONNECTS]
-[SIGHS]

20:33.433 --> 20:34.934
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

20:35.900 --> 20:37.600
Come on, quick. Here it comes.

20:41.200 --> 20:42.600
[MONSTER ROARING]

20:43.100 --> 20:46.133
<i>Hey, buddy, listen up.</i>
<i>That's the best punch</i>

20:46.200 --> 20:47.767
<i>in the world hanging up there.</i>

20:50.133 --> 20:51.200
I think that's me.

20:51.533 --> 20:55.333
<i>You aren't even good enough to</i>
<i>pop the top on a bottle of that punch.</i>

20:55.400 --> 20:57.834
<i>So listen up.</i>
<i>This is how it's going to work.</i>

20:59.567 --> 21:01.667
<i>You're going to stop hogging</i>
<i>all the punch</i>

21:01.734 --> 21:04.900
<i>and I'll let you</i>
<i>keep your kneecaps! Yes?</i>

21:05.834 --> 21:07.300
<i>I'm glad you're down with it.</i>

21:07.367 --> 21:09.000
SAM: Hey, you never
said any of that stuff.

21:09.066 --> 21:11.400
<i>Now let's go get some punch!</i>

21:11.900 --> 21:13.333
ANNOUNCER: <i>Cardio Punch,</i>

21:13.433 --> 21:16.533
<i>the drink of spiky-headed,</i>
<i>tough kids everywhere.</i>

21:19.100 --> 21:20.433
Thank you, thank you.

21:21.133 --> 21:22.133
That was me.

21:25.533 --> 21:28.100
You're looking at the new spokesfamily

21:28.166 --> 21:31.333
for Cardio Powertime Punch... No.

21:31.633 --> 21:33.767
You're looking at the new spokesfamily

21:33.834 --> 21:36.567
for Cardio Punch Power Drink.

21:36.633 --> 21:38.867
[STOMPING FOOT]

21:38.934 --> 21:42.467
I can't get it.
Cardio Punch Sports Drink.

21:42.834 --> 21:44.567
This casting lady in the mall...

21:45.200 --> 21:46.367
-[LAUGHING] What a...
-WOMAN: One more.

21:47.600 --> 21:48.734
There goes the strawberries.

21:50.500 --> 21:53.233
This is going nowhere.
And there's a big... Whoa!

21:53.734 --> 21:54.867
<i>And sometimes we make it</i>

21:54.934 --> 21:56.033
MAN: Put 'em down. Put 'em down.

21:56.100 --> 21:57.667
I'm singing our theme song, man.

21:57.734 --> 21:58.734
MAN: You look like a stalker.

21:59.600 --> 22:01.133
[LAUGHING] A stalker.

22:02.400 --> 22:04.400
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
